29/01/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Hundreds of litres of oil and salt water spilled early Monday (January 28th) from a ruptured pipe into the Sabar River in southern Romania.
Crews are working to clean up the area near the town of Leordeni and curb the environmental impact.
In other news, parliament is set to debate ratification of the EU's Treaty of Lisbon next week.
French President Nikolas Sarkozy, who will be in Bucharest at the time, will address lawmakers before they vote.
(AP, Rompres, Hotnews.ro, BTA, BNR - 28/01/08)
